(380, 1, '2022-11-16 12:17:32', '2022-11-16 12:17:32', '<h1>ERC Program Los Angeles</h1> \r\n\r\nHow Does The ERC (Employee Retention Credit) Program Affect Businesses In Los Angeles?\r\nEligible Los Angeles firms who saw significant drops in their gross receipts in 2020 and 2021 as a result of the COVID-19 epidemic may be eligible for the ERC, a refundable tax credit. The ERC\'s amount is determined by the salary given to the workers they continued to pay. \r\nThe majority of Los Angeles companies, including colleges, universities, hospitals, and 501(c) organizations, are still eligible for the credit. In order to qualify for the credit, an eligible company must demonstrate that one of the following applied during the quarter in question:\r\n1. Due to a government order, operations ceased entirely or partially, or hours were shortened. Only the period during which business was suspended may be claimed for the ERC.\r\n2. The company\'s gross receipts significantly decreased. The company had to demonstrate a gross receipts reduction of more than 50% from the same quarter in 2019 in order to be eligible for the credit in 2020. The employer just required to demonstrate a decrease of more than 20% from the same quarter in 2019 to be eligible for the credit for 2021.\r\nIf your company took out a Paycheck Protection Program (PPP) loan, you may still be eligible for the ERC for wages that weren\'t paid with the money from the forgiven component of the loan. At QuiqLoans you can easily qualify for ERC program in Los Angeles.\r\n\r\nHOW TO SUBMIT A CREDIT FOR EMPLOYEE RETENTION\r\nEmployers who believe they qualify for the ERC may include a claim for it on their Form 941, Employer\'s Quarterly Federal Tax Return, which is used to file federal employment tax filings. A business may file an updated Form 941 requesting the credit if it first does not claim it but later realises it is qualified. On their Form 944, Employer\'s Annual Federal Tax Return, or other employer\'s return, certain businesses may additionally claim the credit.\r\nEmployers may request an advance on employer credits by submitting Form 7200, Advance Payment of Employer Credits Due to COVID-19, when their employment taxes paid are insufficient to fully pay the ERC. Businesses established after December 31, 2020, however, are not eligible to submit a Form 7200 for an advance payment of the credit. \r\n', 'ERC program Los Angeles', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'erc-program-los-angeles', '', '', '2023-03-22 11:25:04', '2023-03-22 11:25:04', '', 0, 'http://localhost/clean_quiqloans/?page_id=380', 0, 'page', '', 0),
